\n<p>We looked at <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/2390220/disk-drill-pro-review.html\">Disk Drill for Mac</a>, a solution for when your Mac hard drive fails and you need to recover data, but what about if the same happens to your iPhone? Here we look at the version of the same software for anyone seeking to recover data from their iPhone. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>When it comes to the <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/668872/best-data-recovery-apps-for-iphone.html\">best data recovery apps for your iPhone</a>, there’s one thing that’s key above all else – simplicity.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>After all, if you’re looking for lost data the last thing you want are complex menus and jargon to dig through, particularly if time is of the essence. Thankfully, <a href=\"https://www.cleverfiles.com/data-recovery-software.html\" target=\"_blank\">Disk Drill</a> makes getting to your data a priority, meaning you can be sifting through your images, videos, or just about anything else within minutes of installing.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’re recovering under 500MB of data, the free plan may work nicely, but things get significantly pricier for the Pro version. It’ll set you back $89/£70.56, with an extra option to add future updates for around $15/£15, too, while enterprise users can buy a bundle of user licenses.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As we’ll cover shortly, in our testing Disk Drill did a great job of, uh, drilling into our test iPhone’s deleted data, but it actually offers additional features on top of data recovery.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Disk Drill can identify duplicate files, spot where your drive may be hoarding data, and can back up copies of files to prevent them from being accidentally deleted in the future.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>First Impressions</h2>\n\n\n<div><figure><img src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Disk-Drill-iPhone-Start.jpeg?quality=50&amp;strip=all&amp;w=1200\" alt=\"Disk Drill iPhone Start\" srcset=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Disk-Drill-iPhone-Start.jpeg?quality=50&amp;strip=all 1397w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Disk-Drill-iPhone-Start.jpeg?resize=300%2C197&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 300w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Disk-Drill-iPhone-Start.jpeg?resize=768%2C505&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 768w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Disk-Drill-iPhone-Start.jpeg?resize=1200%2C789&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1200w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Disk-Drill-iPhone-Start.jpeg?resize=150%2C100&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 150w\" width=\"1200\" height=\"789\" loading=\"lazy\" />\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<figcaption><strong>Disk Drill looks like it could have been made by Apple</strong>.</figcaption>\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t<div><div><figure><img alt=\"Disk Drill iPhone Start\" srcset=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Disk-Drill-iPhone-Start.jpeg?quality=50&amp;strip=all 1397w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Disk-Drill-iPhone-Start.jpeg?resize=300%2C197&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 300w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Disk-Drill-iPhone-Start.jpeg?resize=768%2C505&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 768w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Disk-Drill-iPhone-Start.jpeg?resize=1200%2C789&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1200w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Disk-Drill-iPhone-Start.jpeg?resize=150%2C100&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 150w\" width=\"1200\" height=\"789\" loading=\"lazy\" /><figcaption><strong>Disk Drill looks like it could have been made by Apple</strong>.</figcaption></figure><p>Foundry</p></div>\n</div>\n\t\t\t\t<div><div><figure><img alt=\"Disk Drill iPhone Start\" srcset=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Disk-Drill-iPhone-Start.jpeg?quality=50&amp;strip=all 1397w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Disk-Drill-iPho